# Alpaca paper trading (https://alpaca.markets/)
ALPACA_API_KEY_ID=
ALPACA_API_SECRET_KEY=
# Market data feed for the price.crossesBelow/crossesAbove watcher (catalog/providers/alpaca.ts):
# "iex" (default) is the real feed — only ticks during US market hours (9:30-16:00 ET, Mon-Fri).
# "test" switches to Alpaca's 24/7 synthetic FAKEPACA feed for off-hours development; same wire
# protocol, only the symbol and stream URL differ. Requires a process restart to change.
ALPACA_DATA_FEED=iex

# SEC EDGAR requires a descriptive User-Agent: "<name> <email>"
EDGAR_USER_AGENT=
# Debug-only forced-fire trick for catalog/providers/edgar.ts (see docs/acceptance-tests.md
# AT-8 step 3): set to "1" to make the very first CIK watch created in this process seed its
# seen-set with every eligible filing except the single most recent one, so the next ~30s poll
# treats that already-existing filing as "new" and fires immediately — useful when no real
# filing will land during a demo (e.g. weekends). Consumed ONCE per process (see
# createSkipLatestSeedConsumer in edgar.ts): only that first watch ever gets the trick, so a
# watch torn down and recreated later in the same long-running process (e.g. disarm +
# re-subscribe) can't keep manufacturing repeat forced wakes. Requires a process restart to
# take effect at all.
# EDGAR_SEED_SKIP_LATEST=1

# LangSmith tracing (https://smith.langchain.com/), wired via agent/instrumentation.ts
# using langsmith's OTel exporter (LangSmithOTLPTraceExporter).
# Optional — without a key (or without LANGSMITH_TRACING=true) tracing is simply
# disabled; the agent itself runs fine:
LANGSMITH_API_KEY=
# Optional — falls back to LangSmith's "default" project when unset:
LANGSMITH_PROJECT=
# LANGSMITH_TRACING must be the literal string "true", or the exporter is a silent
# no-op — it checks this before ever sending spans, with no error either way.
LANGSMITH_TRACING=true
# Optional — only for self-hosted/EU LangSmith; defaults to api.smith.langchain.com:
# LANGSMITH_ENDPOINT=
# Note: spans export in batches (~5s delay). Stopping the server immediately after a
# request can lose the trailing batch — finish a demo, wait a beat, then kill the server.

# Model access via Vercel AI Gateway. Locally, `vercel link` + `vercel env pull`
# populates VERCEL_OIDC_TOKEN in .env.local instead, which also satisfies this.
AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY=

# Catalog registry + conversation map (Upstash Redis via Vercel Marketplace:
# `vercel integration add upstash/upstash-kv`, then `vercel env pull`).
# @upstash/redis reads either naming convention; only one pair is needed.
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=
# KV_REST_API_URL=
# KV_REST_API_TOKEN=

# Base URL catalog/wake.ts uses to loop back into this same server's own
# POST /catalog/wake route when delivering a wake (expiry timers, provider
# ticks, and agent/schedules/market-open.ts's own residual POST
# /catalog/chat). Optional there — resolveCatalogBaseUrl (catalog/wake.ts)
# otherwise derives it: on Vercel, from the auto-injected VERCEL_URL (as
# https://$VERCEL_URL); locally, http://localhost:$PORT (PORT defaults to
# 2000). Set this explicitly only if neither derivation is right for your
# environment (e.g. a custom domain you want loopback calls to use instead
# of the raw VERCEL_URL).
#
# REQUIRED on the deployed connector service specifically: connector/lib/
# deliver-wake.ts's own CATALOG_BASE_URL export has no VERCEL_URL fallback,
# and connector/routes/market-open-turn.get.ts (the operative market-open
# transport on Vercel Services — see CAMPAIGN_CONVERSATION_ID below) reads
# it via resolveMarketOpenBaseUrl (connector/lib/market-open-turn.ts), which
# throws at request time rather than silently defaulting to localhost
# whenever it's unset in a deployed (VERCEL env marker present) context.
# Provision it as a real project env var for the connector service — an
# unset value there fails loudly instead of 404ing every market-open turn
# into the void.
# CATALOG_BASE_URL=http://localhost:2000

# Shared secret gating POST /catalog/chat and POST /catalog/wake (AT-10):
# callers send `authorization: Bearer $CATALOG_API_SECRET`. Required — the
# server refuses to boot without it (catalog/auth.ts's
# assertCatalogApiSecretConfigured), rather than silently running those write
# routes unauthenticated. GET /catalog/subscriptions and GET /catalog/events
# stay open, no secret needed. Provision via
# `vercel env add CATALOG_API_SECRET development` (a generated random value),
# then `vercel env pull` — never hand-edit this file (see KNOWN_ISSUES.md #2).
CATALOG_API_SECRET=

# Pure runaway/loop protection (catalog/turn-cap.ts) — NOT a cost cap, and
# deliberately the only guardrail of its kind (paper trading + full autonomy
# is the intended posture; see docs/plan-vercel-production.md Phase 4). A
# per-UTC-day ceiling on turns started, shared across POST /catalog/chat and
# POST /catalog/wake. Optional — falls back to 200/day when unset or set to
# a non-positive/non-numeric value.
# MAX_TURNS_PER_DAY=200

# conversationId of the ONE perpetual standing-mandate campaign conversation
# (docs/plan-vercel-production.md Phase 4, DECIDED 2026-07-13), read by
# whichever market-open transport is actually live in your deployment. On
# Vercel Services (production, as of 2026-07-14) that's the connector's own
# GET /market-open-turn Cron route (connector/routes/market-open-turn.get.ts,
# connector/lib/market-open-turn.ts) — eve's own defineSchedule cron
# (agent/schedules/market-open.ts) does not register there and stays only
# as the transport for a non-Services eve-native environment. Both POST the
# SAME "market's open" turn to this conversation, every market weekday at
# 13:30 UTC — never hardcode the conversationId (e.g. "campaign-5") in
# code; a fresh campaign gets a new id and this is the one place that needs
# updating. Required for either transport to do anything; both silently
# no-op (with a log line) when unset.
CAMPAIGN_CONVERSATION_ID=

# This paper account's opening equity — the baseline the observatory's
# Campaign page derives realized P&L from (observatory/lib/portfolio-metrics.ts's
# computeRealizedPnl), read server-side by observatory/app/campaign/page.tsx.
# Optional — falls back to 100000 when unset, non-numeric, or non-positive.
CAMPAIGN_INITIAL_EQUITY=

# Base URL for the eve app's public read-only GETs, consumed by the
# observatory workspace's proxy routes (observatory/lib/catalog-source.ts).
# Optional — defaults to http://localhost:2000 for local dev; set this when
# the observatory is deployed separately from the eve app it observes.
CATALOG_API_BASE_URL=

# Fail-closed bearer secret for every connector service route (start*,
# ensure-*, smoke-test, status, stop-run — connector/lib/auth.ts's
# requireCronSecret). Vercel's own convention (vercel.com/docs/cron-jobs):
# once set as a project env var, Vercel auto-attaches `authorization: Bearer
# $CRON_SECRET` on the four routes registered as Crons in root vercel.json;
# the other seven manual/smoke-test routes need the same header supplied by
# hand. Required — every connector route 503s without it rather than
# silently running open.
CRON_SECRET=
